{
  "texts": [
    "The one explored in this Thesis is Domain Specificity.",
    "Domain Specific Training TrainingBoth BERT [19] and RoBERTa [16] used well-known pre-training corpora, such as CC NEWS [46] and the Book Corpus [74].Unlike BERT, which employs a static masking strategy, RoBERTa dynamically masks a random selection of tokens during each training epoch.",
    "When selecting a neural network for pre-training, the most influential considerations are both the size and quality of the data [52].",
    "The data quality is even more important when pre-training for a domain-specific model.",
    "The PubMedBERT model [28] uses only PubMed data, which works well in the biomedical field as the data is high quality and numerous."
  ]
}